OL,6,FBoothby who had convictions for 32
OL,7,Fprevious offences had been jailed for
OL,8,Fthree years in November 2016 for
OL,9,Frobbery and possessing a blade.
OL,11,FHe had also been jailed for 14 months
OL,12,Fin March 2021 for theft and
OL,13,Fthreatening someone with an offensive
OL,14,Fweapon.
OL,16,FRecorder Taryn Turner said that it was
OL,17,Fa very serious offence. "You
OL,18,Fpreviously heard comments or talk
OL,19,Fabout the complainant and you took
OL,20,Fexception to him living in the
OL,21,Flocale," said Recorder Turner.
